# Vue 3 + TypeScript

## Structure

```
src/
  api/              # apiFetch, typed endpoints, parseApiError
  components/       # presentational .vue
  composables/      # useAuth, useFlights, useSettings
  views/            # route-level pages
  router/           # vue-router
  types/            # generated from openapi/schema.yaml
  App.vue
  main.ts
```

## Patterns

- **Composition API** + `<script setup lang="ts">`
- One `api/client.ts` — all fetch through CSRF-aware wrapper
- **Composables** for data fetching; views/components stay thin
- Explicit `loading` / `error` / `empty` states in templates
- Prefer native `fetch` over axios (cookies + CSRF simpler)
- **Pinia** optional — fine for auth user; composables alone also work

## Auth

- App init: `GET /auth/me` — `null` body or 401/403 → logged out
- Login: full-page redirect to `/auth/google` on the API host
- OAuth return: backend redirects to `FRONTEND_URL?auth=success|error` — read query in router guard or `App.vue`, then refetch user

## Env

- `VITE_API_URL` only — never commit secrets
- Vite dev server default `:5173` — add to backend `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`

## Testing

- Vitest + `@vue/test-utils` for components
- Mock `api/client` in composable tests
- E2E: backend `:8000`, frontend `:5173`, real session flow
